// D&D 5e Backgrounds Data — auto-extracted from player.html

var BACKGROUNDS=[
// ══ PHB 2014 ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
{name:"Acolyte",src:0,skills:["Insight","Religion"],tools:[],languages:"Two of your choice",equipment:"Holy symbol, prayer book or wheel, 5 sticks of incense, vestments, common clothes, 15 gp",feature:"Shelter of the Faithful",featureDesc:"As an acolyte, you command the respect of those who share your faith. You and your adventuring companions can expect free healing and care at temples of your faith, and those affiliated will support you (though you must provide any material components). You have ties to a specific temple where you have a residence. This could be a source of aid or information, but also creates obligations.",description:"You have spent your life in the service of a temple to a specific god or pantheon of gods. You act as an intermediary between the realm of the holy and the mortal world, performing sacred rites and offering sacrifices in order to conduct worshipers into the presence of the divine. You aren't necessarily a cleric — performing sacred rites is not the same thing as channeling divine power. You can choose a god, a pantheon of gods, or some other quasi-divine being, and work with your DM to detail the nature of your religious service. Personality Traits (d8), Ideals (d6), Bonds (d6), and Flaws (d6) tables are available in the PHB.",abv:""},
{name:"Charlatan",src:0,skills:["Deception","Sleight of Hand"],tools:["Disguise kit","Forgery kit"],languages:"—",equipment:"Fine clothes, disguise kit, tools of the con of your choice, 15 gp",feature:"False Identity",featureDesc:"You have created a second identity that includes documentation, established acquaintances, and disguises. Additionally, you can forge documents including official papers and personal letters, as long as you have seen an example of the kind of document or the handwriting you are trying to copy.",description:"You have always had a way with people. You know what makes them tick, you can tease out their desires after a few minutes of conversation, and with a few leading questions you can read them like they were children's books. It's a useful talent, and one that you're perfectly willing to use for your advantage. You know what people want and you deliver — or rather, you promise to deliver. Common sense should steer you clear of a life of crime, but the penalties if you get caught and the moral questions involved are just challenges that need to be overcome.",abv:""},
{name:"Criminal",src:0,skills:["Deception","Stealth"],tools:["One type of gaming set","Thieves' tools"],languages:"—",equipment:"Crowbar, dark common clothes with a hood, 15 gp",feature:"Criminal Contact",featureDesc:"You have a reliable and trustworthy contact who acts as your liaison to a network of other criminals. You know how to get messages to and from your contact, even over great distances; specifically, you know the local messengers, corrupt caravan masters, and seedy sailors who can deliver messages for you.",description:"You are an experienced criminal with a history of breaking the law. You have spent a lot of time among other criminals and still have contacts within the criminal underworld. You're far closer than most people to the world of murder, theft, and violence that pervades the underbelly of civilization, and you have survived up to this point by flouting the rules and regulations of society. Personality Traits (d8), Ideals (d6), Bonds (d6), and Flaws (d6) tables are available in the PHB.",abv:""},
{name:"Entertainer",src:0,skills:["Acrobatics","Performance"],tools:["Disguise kit","One type of musical instrument"],languages:"—",equipment:"Musical instrument (one of your choice), the favor of an admirer, costume, 15 gp",feature:"By Popular Demand",featureDesc:"You can always find a place to perform, usually in an inn or tavern but possibly with a circus, at a theater, or even in a noble's court. At such a place, you receive free lodging and food of a modest or comfortable standard (depending on the quality of the establishment), as long as you perform each night. In addition, your performance makes you something of a local figure. When strangers recognize you in a town where you have performed, they typically take a liking to you.",description:"You thrive in front of an audience. You know how to entrance them, entertain them, and even inspire them. Your poignant dances tell stories, your comedic acts can make a dour lord muster a fleeting smile, and your music can cause the weary to forget their burdens for a short while. Maybe you learned your craft in a troupe of wandering acrobats, at the knee of a master puppeteer, as a member of a bards college, or by long hours of practice.",abv:""},
{name:"Folk Hero",src:0,skills:["Animal Handling","Survival"],tools:["One type of artisan's tools","Vehicles (land)"],languages:"—",equipment:"Artisan's tools (one of your choice), shovel, iron pot, common clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Rustic Hospitality",featureDesc:"Since you come from the ranks of the common folk, you fit in among them with ease. You can find a place to hide, rest, or recuperate among other commoners, unless you have shown yourself to be a danger to them. They will shield you from the law or anyone else searching for you, though they will not risk their lives for you.",description:"You come from a humble social rank, but you are destined for so much more. Already the people of your home village regard you as their champion, and your destiny calls you to stand against the tyrants and monsters that threaten the common folk everywhere. Defining event (d10) table included in PHB.",abv:""},
{name:"Guild Artisan",src:0,skills:["Insight","Persuasion"],tools:["One type of artisan's tools"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Artisan's tools (one of your choice), letter of introduction from your guild, traveler's clothes, 15 gp",feature:"Guild Membership",featureDesc:"As an established and respected member of a guild, you can rely on certain benefits that membership provides. Your fellow guild members will provide you with lodging and food if necessary, and pay for your funeral if needed. In some cities and towns, a guild hall offers a central place to meet other members of your profession, which can be a good place to meet potential patrons, allies, or hirelings. Guilds often wield tremendous political power. If you are accused of a crime, your guild will support you if a good case can be made for your innocence or if the crime is justifiable. You must pay dues of 5 gp per month to the guild.",description:"You are a member of an artisan's guild, skilled in a particular field and closely associated with other artisans. You are a well-established part of the mercantile world, freed by talent and wealth from the constraints of a feudal social order. You learned your skills as an apprentice to a master artisan, under the sponsorship of your guild, until you became a master in your own right.",abv:""},
{name:"Hermit",src:0,skills:["Medicine","Religion"],tools:["Herbalism kit"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Scroll case stuffed full of notes from your studies or prayers, winter blanket, common clothes, herbalism kit, 5 gp",feature:"Discovery",featureDesc:"The quiet seclusion of your extended hermitage gave you access to a unique and powerful discovery. The exact nature of this revelation depends on the nature of your seclusion. It might be a great truth about the cosmos, the deities, the powerful beings of the outer planes, or the forces of nature. It could be a site that no one else has ever seen. You might have uncovered a fact that has long been forgotten, or unearthed some relic of the past that could rewrite history. It might be information that would be damaging to the people who or institution that expelled you from society.",description:"You lived in seclusion — either in a sheltered community such as a monastery, or entirely alone — for a formative part of your life. In your time apart from the clamor of society, you found quiet, solitude, and perhaps some of the answers you were looking for.",abv:""},
{name:"Noble",src:0,skills:["History","Persuasion"],tools:["One type of gaming set"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Fine clothes, signet ring, scroll of pedigree, purse containing 25 gp",feature:"Position of Privilege",featureDesc:"Thanks to your noble birth, people are inclined to think the best of you. You are welcome in high society, and people assume you have the right to be wherever you are. The common folk make every effort to accommodate you and avoid your displeasure, and other people of high birth treat you as a member of the same social sphere. You can secure an audience with a local noble if you need to.",description:"You understand wealth, power, and privilege. You carry a noble title, and your family owns land, collects taxes, and wields significant political influence. You might be a pampered aristocrat unfamiliar with hard work or discomfort, an former merchant just elevated to the nobility, or a disinherited scoundrel with a disproportionate sense of entitlement. Or you could be an honest, hard-working landowner who cares deeply about the people who live and work on your land, keenly aware of your responsibility to them.",abv:""},
{name:"Outlander",src:0,skills:["Athletics","Survival"],tools:["One type of musical instrument"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Staff, hunting trap, trophy from an animal you killed, traveler's clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Wanderer",featureDesc:"You have an excellent memory for maps and geography, and you can always recall the general layout of terrain, settlements, and other features around you. In addition, you can find food and fresh water for yourself and up to five other people each day, provided that the land offers berries, small game, water, and so forth.",description:"You grew up in the wilds, far from civilization and the comforts of town and technology. You've witnessed the migration of herds larger than forests, survived weather more extreme than any city-dweller could comprehend, and enjoyed the solitude of being the only thinking creature for miles in any direction.",abv:""},
{name:"Sage",src:0,skills:["Arcana","History"],tools:[],languages:"Two of your choice",equipment:"Bottle of black ink, quill, small knife, letter from a dead colleague posing a question you have not yet been able to answer, common clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Researcher",featureDesc:"When you attempt to learn or recall a piece of lore, if you do not know that information, you often know where and from whom you can obtain it. Usually, this information comes from a library, scriptorium, university, or a sage or other learned person or creature. Your DM might rule that the knowledge you seek is secreted away in an almost inaccessible place, or that it simply cannot be found. Unearthing the deepest secrets of the multiverse can require an adventure or even a whole campaign.",description:"You spent years learning the lore of the multiverse. You scoured manuscripts, studied scrolls, and listened to the greatest experts on the subjects that interest you. Your efforts have made you a master in your fields of study.",abv:""},
{name:"Sailor",src:0,skills:["Athletics","Perception"],tools:["Navigator's tools","Vehicles (water)"],languages:"—",equipment:"Belaying pin (club), 50 feet of silk rope, lucky charm such as a rabbit foot or small stone with a hole in the center, common clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Ship's Passage",featureDesc:"When you need to, you can secure free passage on a sailing ship for yourself and your adventuring companions. You might sail on the ship you served on, or another ship you have good relations with (perhaps one captained by a former crewmate). Because you're calling in a favor, you can't be certain of a schedule or route that will meet your every need. Your DM will determine how long it takes to get where you need to go. In return for your free passage, you and your companions are expected to assist the crew during the voyage.",description:"You sailed the seas for years, either in the navy of a kingdom, as a privateer, or aboard a merchant vessel. You've seen things that would make a landlubber blanch, and you know that the sea offers both opportunity and peril in equal measure. Your time at sea has made you tough and resourceful, and has given you a wealth of practical skills.",abv:""},
{name:"Soldier",src:0,skills:["Athletics","Intimidation"],tools:["One type of gaming set","Vehicles (land)"],languages:"—",equipment:"Insignia of rank, trophy taken from a fallen enemy, set of bone dice or deck of cards, common clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Military Rank",featureDesc:"You have a military rank from your career as a soldier. Soldiers loyal to your former military organization still recognize your authority and influence, and they defer to you if they are of a lower rank. You can invoke your rank to exert influence over other soldiers and requisition simple equipment or horses for temporary use. You can also usually gain access to friendly military encampments and fortresses where your rank is recognized.",description:"War has been your life for as long as you care to remember. You trained as a youth, studied the use of weapons and armor, learned basic survival techniques, including how to stay alive on the battlefield. You might have been part of a standing national army or a mercenary company, or perhaps a member of a local militia who rose to prominence during a recent war.",abv:""},
{name:"Urchin",src:0,skills:["Sleight of Hand","Stealth"],tools:["Disguise kit","Thieves' tools"],languages:"—",equipment:"Small knife, map of the city you grew up in, pet mouse, token to remember your parents by, common clothes, 10 gp",feature:"City Secrets",featureDesc:"You know the secret patterns and flow to cities and can find passages through the urban sprawl that others would miss. When you are not in combat, you (and companions you lead) can travel between any two locations in the city twice as fast as your speed would normally allow.",description:"You grew up on the streets alone, orphaned, and poor. You had no one to watch over you or to provide for you, so you learned to provide for yourself. You fought fiercely over food and kept a constant watch out for other desperate souls who might steal from you. You slept on rooftops or in alleyways, exposed to the elements, and endured sickness without the advantage of medicine or a place to recuperate.",abv:""},
// ══ PHB 2014 via SCAG ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
{name:"City Watch",src:2,skills:["Athletics","Insight"],tools:[],languages:"Two of your choice",equipment:"Uniform of your city guard, horn to summon help, manacles, 10 gp",feature:"Watcher's Eye",featureDesc:"Your experience in enforcing the law, and dealing with lawbreakers, gives you a feel for local laws and criminals. You can easily find the local outpost of the watch or a similar organization, and just as easily pick out the dens of criminal activity in a community, although you're more likely to be welcome in the former establishment than the latter.",description:"You have served the community where you grew up, standing as its first line of defense against crime. You aren't a soldier, directing your gaze outward at possible enemies. Instead, your service to your hometown was to help police its populace, protecting the citizenry from lawbreakers and malefactors of every stripe. You may have been part of the City Watch of Waterdeep, the baton-wielding police force of the City of Splendors, or a member of the Flaming Fist of Baldur's Gate, which serves as both army and police force.",abv:""},
{name:"Clan Crafter",src:2,skills:["History","Insight"],tools:["One type of artisan's tools"],languages:"Dwarvish or one other if already known",equipment:"Artisan's tools (one of your choice), maker's mark chisel, traveler's clothes, 5 gp plus a gem worth 10 gp",feature:"Respect of the Stout Folk",featureDesc:"As well respected as clan crafters are among outsiders, no one esteems them quite so highly as dwarves do. You always have free room and board in any place where shield dwarves or gold dwarves dwell, and the individuals in such a settlement might vie for the honor of hosting you.",description:"The Stout Folk are well known for their artisanship and the worth of their handiwork, and you have been trained in that ancient tradition. For years you labored under a dwarf master of the craft, enduring long hours, and dismissive, curmudgeonly treatment in order to gain the fine skills you possess today.",abv:""},
{name:"Cloistered Scholar",src:2,skills:["History"],tools:[],languages:"Two of your choice",equipment:"Borrowed book on the subject of your current study, scholar's robes, writing kit, 10 gp",feature:"Library Access",featureDesc:"Though others must often endure extensive interviews and significant fees to gain access to even the most common archives in your library, you have free access to the majority of the library, though it might also have repositories of lore that are too valuable, magical, or secret to permit anyone immediate access. You have a working knowledge of your cloister's personnel and bureaucracy, and you know how to navigate those connections with some ease.",description:"You have spent your formative years as a privileged member of a library, whether that means the stacks of Candlekeep or the tower libraries of a university of magic. You were allowed access to its vast storerooms of knowledge, and in between your other studies, you've learned much from all the books and scrolls there.",abv:""},
{name:"Courtier",src:2,skills:["Insight","Persuasion"],tools:[],languages:"Two of your choice",equipment:"Fine clothes, 5 gp",feature:"Court Functionary",featureDesc:"Your knowledge of how bureaucracies function lets you gain access to the records and inner workings of any noble court or government you encounter. You know who the movers and shakers are, whom to go to for the favors you seek, and what the current intrigues of interest in the group are.",description:"In your earlier days, you were a personage of some significance in a noble court or a bureaucratic organization. You might or might not come from an upper-class family; your talents, rather than the circumstances of your birth, could have secured you this position. You might have been one of the many functionaries, attendants, and other hangers-on in the Court of Silverymoon, or perhaps you traveled in Waterdeep's baroque and sometimes cutthroat conglomeration of guilds, nobles, adventurers, and secret societies.",abv:""},
{name:"Faction Agent",src:2,skills:["Insight"],tools:[],languages:"Two of your choice",equipment:"Badge or emblem of your faction, copy of a seminal text of your faction, common clothes, 15 gp",feature:"Safe Haven",featureDesc:"As a faction agent, you have access to a secret network of supporters and operatives who can provide assistance on your adventures. You know a set of secret signs and passwords you can use to identify such operatives, who can provide you with access to a hidden safe house, free room and board, or assistance in finding information. These agents never risk their lives for you or risk revealing their true identities.",description:"You are an agent of one of the Sword Coast's many factions. You might be a Harper, a member of the Order of the Gauntlet, a Zhentarim agent, an Emerald Enclave scout, or a member of the Lords' Alliance.",abv:""},
{name:"Far Traveler",src:2,skills:["Insight","Perception"],tools:["One musical instrument or gaming set"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"One set of traveler's clothes, any one musical instrument or gaming set you are proficient with, poorly wrought maps from your homeland, small piece of jewelry worth 10 gp in the style of your homeland, 5 gp",feature:"All Eyes on You",featureDesc:"Your accent, mannerisms, figures of speech, and perhaps even your appearance all mark you as foreign. Curious glances are directed your way wherever you go, which can be an nuisance, but you also gain the friendly interest of scholars and others intrigued by far-off lands, to say nothing of everyday folk who are eager to hear stories of your homeland. You can parley this attention into access to people and places you might not otherwise have, for you and your traveling companions. Noble lords, scholars, and merchant princes might be interested in hearing about your distant homeland and people.",description:"Almost all of the common folk and other people of the Sword Coast have heard of the great powers of the region: Baldur's Gate, Waterdeep, Amn, the empire of Netheril, and others. But you are not from any of those places. You are from one of the many distant lands beyond the western horizon — perhaps Calimshan, Kara-Tur, Thay, or somewhere further.",abv:""},
{name:"Inheritor",src:2,skills:["Survival"],tools:["One gaming set or musical instrument"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Inheritance item, traveler's clothes, 15 gp",feature:"Inheritance",featureDesc:"Choose or randomly determine your inheritance from among the possibilities in the table in SCAG. Work with your DM to determine the origin and the nature of your inheritance. The item was given to you as a gift or handed to you directly; it might have been left in the care of a guardian, to be passed on when you came of age. Alternatively, it might be an object your family has looked after for generations, with an associated legend or mystical significance.",description:"You are the heir to something of great value — not mere coin or wealth, but an object, position, or legacy that was entrusted to you and you alone. Your inheritance might have come directly to you from a member of your family, by royal decree, or even because of a prophecy.",abv:""},
{name:"Knight of the Order",src:2,skills:["Persuasion"],tools:["One gaming set or musical instrument"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Uniform or emblem of your order, traveler's clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Knightly Regard",featureDesc:"You receive shelter and succor from members of your knightly order and those who are sympathetic to its aims. If your order is a religious one, you can gain aid from temples and other religious communities of your deity. Knights of civic orders can obtain help from the community — whether a town or a noble — that they serve, and knights of philosophical orders can find help from those they have aided in the past and those who support the order's ideals.",description:"You belong to an order of knights who have sworn oaths to achieve a certain goal. The nature of this goal depends on the order you serve.",abv:""},
{name:"Mercenary Veteran",src:2,skills:["Athletics","Persuasion"],tools:["One type of gaming set","Vehicles (land)"],languages:"—",equipment:"Uniform of your mercenary company, insignia of your rank, gaming set, 10 gp",feature:"Mercenary Life",featureDesc:"You know the mercenary life as only someone who has experienced it can. You are able to identify mercenary companies by their emblems, and you know a little about any such company, including the names and reputations of its commanders and leaders, and who has hired them recently. You can find the taverns and festhalls that mercenaries frequent in any area, as long as you speak the language. You can find mercenary work between adventures sufficient to maintain a comfortable lifestyle.",description:"As a sell-sword who fought battles for coin, you're well acquainted with risking life and limb for a chance at a share of treasure. Now, you look forward to fighting foes and reaping even greater rewards as an adventurer. Your experience makes you well traveled, gives you a knowledge of the world, and helps you avoid legal complications.",abv:""},
{name:"Urban Bounty Hunter",src:2,skills:["Two of: Deception, Insight, Persuasion, Stealth"],tools:["Two of: thieves' tools, disguise kit, gaming set, musical instrument"],languages:"—",equipment:"A set of clothes appropriate to your duties, tools of your trade, 20 gp",feature:"Ear to the Ground",featureDesc:"You are in frequent contact with people in the segment of society that your chosen quarries move through. These people might not be honest citizens, but they have their own code of honor or look out for their own. Cheating them or going back on your promises can be dangerous. Among such folk, you have a contact who offers you information in return for compensation: you supply the payment (usually coin, favors, or information), and the contact provides the information.",description:"Before you became an adventurer, your life was already full of conflict and excitement, because you made a living tracking down people for pay. Unlike some people who collect bounties, though, you aren't a savage who follows quarry into or through the wilderness. You're involved in a lucrative trade, in the place where you live, that routinely tests your skills and survival instincts.",abv:""},
{name:"Uthgardt Tribe Member",src:2,skills:["Athletics","Survival"],tools:["One type of musical instrument or artisan's tools"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Hunting trap, large hide sack, totemic object or set of tattoos, traveler's clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Uthgardt Heritage",featureDesc:"You have an excellent knowledge of not only your tribe's territory, but also the terrain and natural resources of the rest of the North. You are familiar enough with any wilderness area that you find twice as much food and water as you normally would when you forage there. Additionally, you can call upon the hospitality of your people, and those allied with your tribe, often including members of druid circles, tribes of the Uthgardt, and even the priests of certain gods whose philosophies and practices closely align with the Uthgardt way of life.",description:"You grew up in one of the many barbarian tribes that roam the vast tundra and forests of the North. You are one of the Uthgardt, a proud people descended from those who first arrived in Faerûn long ago.",abv:""},
{name:"Waterdhavian Noble",src:2,skills:["History","Persuasion"],tools:["One type of gaming set or musical instrument"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Fine clothes, signet ring or brooch, scroll of pedigree, skin of fine zzar or wine, 20 gp",feature:"Kept in Style",featureDesc:"While you are in Waterdeep or elsewhere in the North, your house sees to your everyday needs. Your name and signet are sufficient to cover most expenses; the coat of arms associated with your family is known everywhere in the North. Your connections can also help you smoothly navigate the nobles' court of Waterdeep.",description:"You are a scion of one of the great noble families of Waterdeep. In Waterdeep, authority derives from the coin, and your family is old money.",abv:""},
// ══ PHB 2024 ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
{name:"Acolyte (2024)",src:1,skills:["Insight","Religion"],tools:["Calligrapher's Supplies"],languages:"Two",equipment:"Book (prayers), calligrapher's supplies, holy symbol, parchment (10 sheets), robe, 8 gp",feature:"Magic Initiate (Divine)",featureDesc:"You gain the Magic Initiate feat with the Divine spell option, choosing Cleric. This represents your sacred training.",description:"[PHB 2024] You devoted yourself to service in a temple, either for a god or a pantheon. In the 2024 rules, Acolyte grants an Origin feat (Magic Initiate — Divine) and two ability score increases (+1 WIS, +1 CHA or another combination), reflecting the streamlined Background-as-Origin-Feat system.",abv:"WIS +1, CHA +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Artisan (2024)",src:1,skills:["Investigation","Persuasion"],tools:["Artisan's Tools (one type)"],languages:"One",equipment:"Artisan's tools (one kind), guild letter of introduction, traveler's clothes, 32 gp",feature:"Magic Initiate (Arcane or Primal)",featureDesc:"You gain the Crafter origin feat, granting proficiency with three additional Artisan's Tools and a 20% discount at shops.",description:"[PHB 2024] You have trained as a craftsperson in a guild or workshop. The Artisan background grants the Crafter origin feat, skill proficiencies in Investigation and Persuasion, and tool proficiency in one artisan's tool set. You also gain the Crafter feat's shop discount.",abv:"STR +1, DEX +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Charlatan (2024)",src:1,skills:["Deception","Sleight of Hand"],tools:["Forgery Kit"],languages:"One",equipment:"Forgery kit, costume, 15 gp",feature:"Skilled (Origin Feat)",featureDesc:"You gain the Skilled origin feat, granting proficiency in three additional skills or tools of your choice.",description:"[PHB 2024] You have always had a way with people. Charlatan background grants the Skilled origin feat (3 more skills/tools), skill proficiencies in Deception and Sleight of Hand, and tool proficiency with a Forgery Kit.",abv:"DEX +1, CHA +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Criminal (2024)",src:1,skills:["Sleight of Hand","Stealth"],tools:["Thieves' Tools"],languages:"One",equipment:"Thieves' tools, crowbar, dark common clothes with hood, 15 gp",feature:"Alert (Origin Feat)",featureDesc:"You gain the Alert origin feat: +2 Initiative, can't be surprised while conscious, and hidden creatures don't gain advantage on attack rolls against you.",description:"[PHB 2024] An experienced criminal with underworld connections. The Criminal background grants the Alert origin feat, skill proficiencies in Sleight of Hand and Stealth, and tool proficiency with Thieves' Tools.",abv:"DEX +1, INT +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Entertainer (2024)",src:1,skills:["Acrobatics","Performance"],tools:["Musical Instrument (one kind)"],languages:"One",equipment:"Musical instrument (one of your choice), costume, 32 gp",feature:"Musician (Origin Feat)",featureDesc:"You gain the Musician origin feat: proficiency with three musical instruments, and when you finish a short rest playing music, a number of allies equal to your Proficiency Bonus who hear it gain Heroic Inspiration.",description:"[PHB 2024] You thrive in front of an audience. Entertainer grants the Musician origin feat, skill proficiencies in Acrobatics and Performance, and instrument proficiency.",abv:"DEX +1, CHA +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Farmer (2024)",src:1,skills:["Animal Handling","Nature"],tools:["Carpenter's Tools"],languages:"One",equipment:"Carpenter's tools, shovel, iron pot, common clothes, 30 gp",feature:"Tough (Origin Feat)",featureDesc:"You gain the Tough origin feat: your HP maximum increases by 2 per level (current and future).",description:"[PHB 2024] New to 2024. You grew up working the land. The Farmer background grants the Tough origin feat (HP +2/level), skill proficiencies in Animal Handling and Nature, and tool proficiency in Carpenter's Tools.",abv:"CON +1, WIS +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Guard (2024)",src:1,skills:["Athletics","Perception"],tools:["Gaming Set (one kind)"],languages:"One",equipment:"Gaming set, hooded lantern, manacles, spear, common clothes, 12 gp",feature:"Alert (Origin Feat)",featureDesc:"You gain the Alert origin feat: +2 Initiative, can't be surprised while conscious, and hidden creatures don't gain advantage on attack rolls against you.",description:"[PHB 2024] You served as a town or city guard. The Guard background grants the Alert origin feat, skill proficiencies in Athletics and Perception, and a gaming set proficiency.",abv:"STR +1, WIS +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Guide (2024)",src:1,skills:["Stealth","Survival"],tools:["Cartographer's Tools"],languages:"One",equipment:"Cartographer's tools, bedroll, tent (one-person), traveler's clothes, 15 gp",feature:"Magic Initiate (Primal)",featureDesc:"You gain the Magic Initiate (Primal) origin feat, choosing Druid spells.",description:"[PHB 2024] You are an experienced wilderness guide. Guide grants the Magic Initiate — Primal origin feat (Druid spells), skill proficiencies in Stealth and Survival, and Cartographer's Tools proficiency.",abv:"DEX +1, WIS +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Hermit (2024)",src:1,skills:["Medicine","Religion"],tools:["Herbalism Kit"],languages:"One",equipment:"Herbalism kit, scroll case with notes, winter blanket, common clothes, 5 gp",feature:"Magic Initiate (Divine)",featureDesc:"You gain the Magic Initiate (Divine) origin feat, choosing Cleric spells.",description:"[PHB 2024] You lived in seclusion for a formative period. Hermit grants Magic Initiate — Divine origin feat, skill proficiencies in Medicine and Religion, and Herbalism Kit proficiency.",abv:"CON +1, WIS +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Merchant (2024)",src:1,skills:["Animal Handling","Persuasion"],tools:["Navigator's Tools"],languages:"One",equipment:"Navigator's tools, 2 pouches, traveler's clothes, 22 gp",feature:"Lucky (Origin Feat)",featureDesc:"You gain the Lucky origin feat: 2 Luck Points per long rest. Spend a point to add 1d6 to any d20 Test result.",description:"[PHB 2024] New to 2024. You worked as a merchant or trader. Merchant grants the Lucky origin feat, skill proficiencies in Animal Handling and Persuasion, and Navigator's Tools proficiency.",abv:"CON +1, CHA +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Noble (2024)",src:1,skills:["History","Persuasion"],tools:["Gaming Set (one kind)"],languages:"One",equipment:"Gaming set, fine clothes, signet ring, 28 gp",feature:"Skilled (Origin Feat)",featureDesc:"You gain the Skilled origin feat: proficiency in any combination of 3 skills or tools of your choice.",description:"[PHB 2024] You were born into or married into a noble family. Noble grants the Skilled origin feat, skill proficiencies in History and Persuasion, and a gaming set proficiency.",abv:"INT +1, CHA +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Sage (2024)",src:1,skills:["Arcana","History"],tools:["Calligrapher's Supplies"],languages:"Two",equipment:"Calligrapher's supplies, book of lore, parchment (8 sheets), common clothes, 8 gp",feature:"Magic Initiate (Arcane)",featureDesc:"You gain the Magic Initiate (Arcane) origin feat, choosing Wizard spells.",description:"[PHB 2024] You spent years learning the lore of the multiverse. Sage grants Magic Initiate — Arcane origin feat (Wizard spells), skill proficiencies in Arcana and History, and Calligrapher's Supplies proficiency.",abv:"INT +1, WIS +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Sailor (2024)",src:1,skills:["Acrobatics","Perception"],tools:["Navigator's Tools"],languages:"One",equipment:"Navigator's tools, silk rope (50 ft), traveler's clothes, 20 gp",feature:"Tavern Brawler (Origin Feat)",featureDesc:"You gain the Tavern Brawler origin feat: proficiency with improvised weapons and unarmed strikes (1d4), bonus grapple after hitting with unarmed/improvised, reroll 1s on such damage.",description:"[PHB 2024] You sailed the seas for years. Sailor grants the Tavern Brawler origin feat, skill proficiencies in Acrobatics and Perception, and Navigator's Tools proficiency.",abv:"STR +1, DEX +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Scribe (2024)",src:1,skills:["Investigation","Perception"],tools:["Calligrapher's Supplies"],languages:"One",equipment:"Calligrapher's supplies, fine clothes, parchment (12 sheets), 23 gp",feature:"Skilled (Origin Feat)",featureDesc:"You gain the Skilled origin feat: proficiency in any combination of 3 skills or tools.",description:"[PHB 2024] New to 2024. You worked copying documents or correspondence. Scribe grants the Skilled origin feat, skill proficiencies in Investigation and Perception, and Calligrapher's Supplies proficiency.",abv:"DEX +1, INT +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Soldier (2024)",src:1,skills:["Athletics","Intimidation"],tools:["Gaming Set (one kind)"],languages:"One",equipment:"Gaming set, rank insignia, traveler's clothes, 14 gp",feature:"Savage Attacker (Origin Feat)",featureDesc:"You gain the Savage Attacker origin feat: once per turn when you roll damage for a melee weapon attack, roll the dice twice and use the higher result.",description:"[PHB 2024] War has been your life. Soldier grants the Savage Attacker origin feat, skill proficiencies in Athletics and Intimidation, and a gaming set proficiency.",abv:"STR +1, CON +1 (or flexible)"},
{name:"Wayfarer (2024)",src:1,skills:["Insight","Stealth"],tools:["Thieves' Tools"],languages:"One",equipment:"Thieves' tools, bedroll, 2 costumes, traveler's clothes, 16 gp",feature:"Lucky (Origin Feat)",featureDesc:"You gain the Lucky origin feat: 2 Luck Points per long rest, add 1d6 to any d20 Test.",description:"[PHB 2024] New to 2024. You grew up as a wanderer or street urchin. Wayfarer grants the Lucky origin feat, skill proficiencies in Insight and Stealth, and Thieves' Tools proficiency.",abv:"DEX +1, WIS +1 (or flexible)"},
// ══ GUILDMASTERS' GUIDE TO RAVNICA ══════════════════════════════════════════
{name:"Azorius Functionary",src:3,skills:["Insight","Intimidation"],tools:[],languages:"Two of your choice",equipment:"Azorius insignia, Ravnican legal code, traveler's clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Legal Authority",featureDesc:"You have the authority to enforce Ravnican law. This allows you to detain individuals suspected of crimes and demand information from witnesses. Azorius soldiers and sphinxes typically defer to you.",description:"You studied law and bureaucracy under the Azorius Senate — Ravnica's foremost lawmakers and law-enforcement agency. You are a functionary steeped in legal tradition, and your guild's complex web of rules and regulations is second nature to you.",abv:""},
{name:"Boros Legionnaire",src:3,skills:["Athletics","Perception"],tools:["One type of gaming set"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Boros insignia, red and white cloak, gaming set, 10 gp",feature:"Legion Station",featureDesc:"You have a rank in the Boros Legion. Your superiors and fellow soldiers recognize this rank and will aid you in matters related to the Legion. You can find lodging and food at any Boros barracks.",description:"You served in the Boros Legion — Ravnica's combined military force and law enforcement body. You are a trained combatant, devoted to justice, who has seen both the glory of battlefield victory and the horror of war.",abv:""},
{name:"Dimir Operative",src:3,skills:["Deception","Stealth"],tools:["Disguise kit"],languages:"Two of your choice",equipment:"Dimir insignia (hidden), disguise kit, common clothes, 10 gp",feature:"False Identity",featureDesc:"You have a carefully constructed false identity and documentation to support it. Acquaintances and contacts see you as part of this false identity. You can also forge documents as in the Charlatan background.",description:"You operate in the shadows for the Dimir — Ravnica's guild of spies, assassins, and mind-mages. You gather secrets for powerful patrons who prefer to remain anonymous, and you are skilled at remaining unseen and unheard.",abv:""},
{name:"Golgari Agent",src:3,skills:["Nature","Survival"],tools:["Poisoner's kit"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Golgari insignia, poisoner's kit, traveler's clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Undercity Contacts",featureDesc:"You have connections to the Undercity — Ravnica's sprawling network of tunnels beneath the streets. You can navigate these tunnels with ease and call on allies among the Golgari there.",description:"You work for the Golgari Swarm — a nature guild that practices a philosophy of death and regrowth, and which provides most of Ravnica's food through mushroom farming in the Undercity. The Golgari are as comfortable with death as with life.",abv:""},
{name:"Gruul Anarch",src:3,skills:["Athletics","Survival"],tools:["Herbalism kit"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Gruul insignia, hunting trophy, traveler's clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Gruul Passage",featureDesc:"You can move through Ravnica's ruined areas and wild spaces without leaving signs of your passage. You also have contacts among other clans of the Gruul who can shelter you.",description:"You belong to the Gruul Clans — the clans of warriors and shamans who reject the civilizing influence of the guilds and seek to return Ravnica to a wilder state. You have survived in the ruins and wild spaces between Ravnica's urban districts.",abv:""},
{name:"Izzet Engineer",src:3,skills:["Arcana","Investigation"],tools:["Artisan's tools (one type)"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Izzet insignia, artisan's tools, traveler's clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Urban Infrastructure",featureDesc:"You have access to Izzet workshops throughout Ravnica. You know where to find experimental equipment and alchemical components, and your guild credentials grant you access to laboratories and arcane infrastructure.",description:"You work for the Izzet League — a guild of mages and engineers who combine magic and technology in spectacular (and often explosive) experiments. Their work powers much of Ravnica's infrastructure.",abv:""},
{name:"Orzhov Representative",src:3,skills:["Intimidation","Religion"],tools:["One type of gaming set"],languages:"Two of your choice",equipment:"Orzhov insignia, fine clothes, gaming set, 20 gp",feature:"Legal Claim",featureDesc:"The Orzhov guild grants you social and legal power. You can invoke the guild's authority to demand repayment of debts, access Orzhov properties, and receive deference from those who owe the guild money or favors.",description:"You serve the Orzhov Syndicate — Ravnica's combination of organized crime and religion. The Orzhov accumulate wealth across generations, their patriarch ghosts hoarding gold even in death. You navigate their complex hierarchy of power.",abv:""},
{name:"Rakdos Cultist",src:3,skills:["Acrobatics","Performance"],tools:["Disguise kit"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Rakdos insignia, costume, performer's tools, 10 gp",feature:"Fearsome Reputation",featureDesc:"Your association with the Rakdos is known, and this instills fear. People will give you and your companions a wide berth, and many will go out of their way to avoid confrontation with you.",description:"You are a performer for the Cult of Rakdos — a demonic circus guild whose shows combine breathtaking acrobatics, sharp-edged comedy, and spectacular violence. Their performances bring chaos and laughter to Ravnica's streets.",abv:""},
{name:"Selesnya Initiate",src:3,skills:["Nature","Persuasion"],tools:["Herbalism kit"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Selesnya insignia, herbalism kit, traveler's clothes, 5 gp",feature:"Conclave's Shelter",featureDesc:"Members of the Selesnya Conclave will provide shelter, food, and healing to you and your companions. Enclaves of the guild exist throughout Ravnica, often in parks and gardens.",description:"You are a member of the Selesnya Conclave — a guild dedicated to unity, nature, and community. Their philosophy is one of collective harmony, and their enclaves are peaceful refuges in Ravnica's often chaotic urban landscape.",abv:""},
{name:"Simic Scientist",src:3,skills:["Medicine","Nature"],tools:["Alchemist's supplies"],languages:"Two of your choice",equipment:"Simic insignia, alchemist's supplies, traveler's clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Researcher",featureDesc:"Same as the Sage's Researcher feature — you know where to seek lore. Additionally, you have access to Simic laboratories and can call on the guild for biological and alchemical expertise.",description:"You work for the Simic Combine — Ravnica's guild of biomancers who blend magic with biology to engineer new life forms and adapt creatures to changing environments. You may have undergone enhancement yourself.",abv:""},
// ══ EBERRON: RISING FROM THE LAST WAR ═══════════════════════════════════════
{name:"House Agent",src:4,skills:["Investigation","Persuasion"],tools:[],languages:"—",equipment:"House signet ring or emblem, traveler's clothes, 20 gp",feature:"House Connections",featureDesc:"You have access to the resources of your dragonmarked house. You can call upon fellow house agents for assistance, and the house's reputation opens doors — literally and figuratively. House facilities (inns, banks, message stations) are available to you.",description:"You are an agent of one of Eberron's dragonmarked houses — powerful mercantile dynasties that wield immense economic and political power across Khorvaire. Your house's dragonmark may or may not manifest in you personally, but you act in the house's interests.",abv:""},
{name:"Haunted One",src:4,skills:["Choose two: Arcana, Investigation, Religion, Survival"],tools:[],languages:"Exotic language of your choice (Abyssal, Celestial, Deep Speech, Draconic, Infernal, Primordial, Sylvan, Undercommon)",equipment:"Monster hunter's pack, Trinket (one from special Haunted One table), 1 gp",feature:"Heart of Darkness",featureDesc:"Those who look into your eyes can see that you have faced unimaginable horror and survived. Though they might fear you, commoners will extend you every courtesy and do their utmost to help. Unless you have shown yourself to be a danger to them, they will even take up arms to fight alongside you, should you find yourself facing an enemy alone.",description:"You are haunted by something so terrible that you dare not speak of it. You've tried to bury it and run away from it, to no avail. Whatever this thing is that haunts you, it can never be fully buried or run away from. Originally from Curse of Strahd, reprinted in Eberron. You have faced the darkness and bear its mark.",abv:""},
{name:"Investigator",src:4,skills:["Insight","Investigation"],tools:[],languages:"Two of your choice",equipment:"Magnifying glass, a set of common clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Official Inquiry",featureDesc:"You can invoke your credentials as an investigator to secure access to a crime scene, secure temporary access to records and official documents, compel reluctant witnesses to cooperate with your inquiries, and gain access to certain restricted areas.",description:"You relentlessly pursue truth and justice wherever it leads, acting as a sleuth in an official or unofficial capacity. Originally from Van Richten's Guide to Ravenloft but reprinted in Eberron resources, the investigator makes their way by asking the right questions — and sometimes the wrong ones.",abv:""},
// ══ EXPLORER'S GUIDE TO WILDEMOUNT ══════════════════════════════════════════
{name:"Augen Trust",src:5,skills:["Deception","Insight"],tools:["Disguise kit","Forgery kit"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Disguise kit, forgery kit, traveler's clothes, 15 gp",feature:"Cloaks and Shadows",featureDesc:"You have a network of safe houses and contacts throughout the Dwendalian Empire. You can send and receive coded messages, obtain temporary shelter, and request information from your handlers.",description:"[Wildemount] You work as a spy for the Augen Trust — the intelligence network of the Dwendalian Empire. Operating in silence and subtlety, you gather secrets and act as the Empire's unseen hand.",abv:""},
{name:"Cobalt Scholar",src:5,skills:["Arcana","History"],tools:["Calligrapher's supplies"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Calligrapher's supplies, book of research notes, common clothes, 15 gp",feature:"Cobalt Soul Researcher",featureDesc:"As an agent of the Cobalt Soul, you have access to the organization's vast libraries and archives. You can make contact with Expositors in major cities for aid, information, and sanctuary.",description:"[Wildemount] You are affiliated with the Cobalt Soul — the great archive-religion of the Knowing Mistress, whose monks dedicate themselves to uncovering truth and hoarding knowledge for the benefit of all.",abv:""},
{name:"Grinner",src:5,skills:["Deception","Performance"],tools:["Disguise kit","One musical instrument"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Disguise kit, musical instrument, traveler's clothes, 15 gp",feature:"Traveler's Cheer",featureDesc:"As a member of the Myriad's covert performance troupe, you can secure safe passage across political borders by posing as a travelling entertainer. Fellow Grinners in any region can provide shelter and information.",description:"[Wildemount] You are a member of the Grinners — a troupe of travelling performers who secretly serve as operatives for the Myriad criminal syndicate. Your cheery facade masks a sharp mind and a sinister network of contacts.",abv:""},
{name:"Revelry Pirate",src:5,skills:["Athletics","Persuasion"],tools:["Navigator's tools","Vehicles (water)"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Navigator's tools, silk rope, common clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Pirate's Passage",featureDesc:"You have connections among the pirates and sailors of the Revelry. In port cities, you can find free passage on ships, secure black market goods, and find shelter in Revelry-friendly establishments.",description:"[Wildemount] You sailed with the Revelry — the confederation of pirates operating out of the Swavain Islands. Free spirits and opportunists, the Revelry preys on shipping lanes and thumbs its nose at authority.",abv:""},
{name:"Volstrucker Agent",src:5,skills:["Deception","Stealth"],tools:["Poisoner's kit"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Poisoner's kit, dark common clothes with hood, 10 gp",feature:"Shadow Network",featureDesc:"You have access to the Volstrucker's network of agents and resources across the Dwendalian Empire. You can call for assistance and send coded messages through the network, and Volstrucker safehouses are available to you.",description:"[Wildemount] You are an agent of the Volstrucker — the clandestine black-ops unit of the Cerberus Assembly. You carry out missions that the Empire's mages cannot officially acknowledge.",abv:""},
// ══ SPELLJAMMER: ADVENTURES IN SPACE ════════════════════════════════════════
{name:"Astral Drifter",src:6,skills:["Insight","Religion"],tools:[],languages:"Two of your choice",equipment:"Astral sequin (shimmers in dim light), traveler's clothes, 14 gp",feature:"Divine Contact",featureDesc:"You drifted through the Astral Plane long enough to encounter a god. This deity has touched your life in some way. You can sometimes receive vague insights or omens from this being, and worshipers of that deity are positively inclined toward you.",description:"[Spelljammer] You have drifted the silver void of the Astral Plane, perhaps for decades, perhaps for centuries, aging little if at all. You've accumulated wisdom from your long journey and a connection to a divine being you met during your travels.",abv:""},
{name:"Wildspacer",src:6,skills:["Athletics","Survival"],tools:["Navigator's tools"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Navigator's tools, 10 days of rations, traveler's clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Wildspace Adaptation",featureDesc:"Living and working in Wildspace has given you an intimate knowledge of spelljammer ships and the hazards of space travel. You know how to identify a ship's type and capabilities, and you have contacts among spelljammer crews in any major port.",description:"[Spelljammer] You grew up on a spelljammer ship or space station, far from any planet. The void of Wildspace is your home, and you are as comfortable navigating between stars as others are walking city streets.",abv:""},
// ══ FIZBAN'S TREASURY OF DRAGONS ════════════════════════════════════════════
{name:"Dragon-Touched",src:7,skills:["Arcana","Survival"],tools:[],languages:"Draconic",equipment:"Dragon-scale armor piece or trophy, traveler's clothes, 15 gp",feature:"Draconic Lore",featureDesc:"Your close connection to dragons (either working for one, being raised by one, or having dragon blood awakened in you) gives you access to draconic knowledge. You can recall facts about dragon lairs, hoards, and history, and a dragon of friendly disposition to you will often answer questions about their kind.",description:"[Fizban's] Your life has been deeply shaped by a connection to a dragon — whether you worked for one as a follower, were left in a dragon's care as a child, or have a dragonshard or scale marking you as a favorite. Dragon-Touched characters often have traces of draconic magic in their bloodline.",abv:""},
// ══ BIGBY PRESENTS: GLORY OF THE GIANTS ════════════════════════════════════
{name:"Giant Foundling",src:8,skills:["Intimidation","Survival"],tools:[],languages:"Giant plus one other",equipment:"Hide armor, greatclub or handaxe, traveler's clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Stone's Endurance (Origin Feat)",featureDesc:"You gain the Stone's Endurance feat (or a background feature similar to it): once per short rest, use a Reaction to reduce incoming damage by 1d12 + CON modifier.",description:"[Glory of Giants] You were raised by giants or among giant-kind, and their culture is as familiar to you as your own. You know the Giant language, the customs of the various giant tribes, and carry with you an outsized perspective on the world — in more ways than one.",abv:""},
{name:"Rune Carver",src:8,skills:["History","Perception"],tools:["Mason's tools or Woodcarver's tools"],languages:"Giant",equipment:"Artisan's tools (mason's or woodcarver's), journal with runic notes, common clothes, 10 gp",feature:"Rune Shaping",featureDesc:"Your knowledge of giant rune magic grants you insight into magical inscriptions. You can identify runes and runic magic, and you know the location of sites where powerful runes are carved (such as giant steadings or ancient stone circles).",description:"[Glory of Giants] You have studied the ancient rune magic of the giants. Whether apprenticed to a rune carver, a self-taught student of the giant's script, or gifted with the knowledge by a divine source, you can read and inscribe runes of power.",abv:""},
// ══ HEROES OF FAERÛN ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
{name:"Baldur's Gate Noble",src:9,skills:["History","Persuasion"],tools:["One gaming set"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Fine clothes, signet ring, letter of invitation from a patriar, 25 gp",feature:"Position of Privilege",featureDesc:"Same as Noble — PHB 2014. Additionally, in Baldur's Gate you are recognized as a patriar (noble family member) and are welcome in the Upper City, receiving deference from commoners and the Flaming Fist.",description:"[Heroes of Faerûn] You are a scion of one of Baldur's Gate's patriar families. You grew up with wealth, education, and social privilege in the Upper City, but the chaos of the city means even nobles must navigate constant intrigue and danger.",abv:""},
{name:"Baldur's Gate Charlatan",src:9,skills:["Deception","Sleight of Hand"],tools:["Disguise kit","Forgery kit"],languages:"—",equipment:"Fine clothes, disguise kit, con tools, 15 gp",feature:"False Identity",featureDesc:"As PHB Charlatan. In Baldur's Gate specifically, your forged identity may include Guild connections or Flaming Fist documents, and you know the city's con networks well.",description:"[Heroes of Faerûn] Baldur's Gate is a city of merchants, criminals, and opportunists. You carved out a place for yourself through deception, and know every angle, every mark, and every back-alley deal in the Lower City.",abv:""},
{name:"Baldurian Patriar",src:9,skills:["History","Intimidation"],tools:["One gaming set"],languages:"One of your choice",equipment:"Fine clothes, signet ring, 30 gp",feature:"Baldur's Gate Influence",featureDesc:"Your family name carries weight in Baldur's Gate's Upper City. You can access the Parliament of Peers with proper notice, arrange meetings with patriar families, and secure deference from the Flaming Fist.",description:"[Heroes of Faerûn] You are a member of one of Baldur's Gate's founding families — a patriar of the Parliament of Peers. Your family holds land, privilege, and enemies, and you must navigate all three.",abv:""},
{"name":"Spy","src":0,"skills":["Deception","Stealth"],"tools":["One type of gaming set","Thieves' tools"],"languages":"—","equipment":"Crowbar, dark common clothes with a hood, 15 gp","feature":"Criminal Contact","featureDesc":"A variant of the Criminal background. You have a reliable and trustworthy contact who acts as your liaison to a network of other spies and criminals. You know how to get messages to and from your contact, even over great distances — through local messengers, corrupt caravan masters, and seedy sailors. Unlike common criminals, your network deals in secrets and information as much as stolen goods.","description":"[PHB 2014 — Criminal variant] You are an experienced operative with a history of covert missions. Rather than common theft, you specialize in information gathering, infiltration, and working for shadowy organizations or intelligence networks. You know how to blend into any environment, construct believable cover identities, and extract what you need without leaving a trace. Your skills are in demand among nobles, merchant guilds, and those who prefer their business conducted quietly.","abv":""},
{"name":"Gladiator","src":0,"skills":["Acrobatics","Performance"],"tools":["Disguise kit","Unusual weapon of your choice"],"languages":"—","equipment":"Inexpensive but unusual weapon (such as a trident or net), the favor of an admirer (love letter, lock of hair, trinket), costume, 15 gp","feature":"By Popular Demand","featureDesc":"A variant of the Entertainer background. You can always find a place to perform — in an arena, gladiatorial pit, or coliseum — and receive free lodging and food of a modest standard as long as you compete or perform. Your reputation as a gladiator makes you something of a local figure wherever you have fought. When strangers recognize you, they typically take a strong interest — whether as fans, rivals, or gamblers who bet on your bouts.","description":"[PHB 2014 — Entertainer variant] You have fought in public arenas for the entertainment of the crowds. Whether you were a slave forced into the pit, a free champion seeking glory, or somewhere between, you have honed your combat skills into a performance. You know how to read a crowd, how to make every strike look purposeful and dramatic, and how to turn even a defensive scramble into a crowd-pleasing spectacle. The roar of the audience is as much a part of your life as the clash of weapons.","abv":""},
{"name":"Knight","src":0,"skills":["History","Persuasion"],"tools":["One type of gaming set"],"languages":"One of your choice","equipment":"Fine clothes, signet ring, scroll of pedigree, purse containing 25 gp","feature":"Retainers","featureDesc":"[Noble variant] You have the service of three retainers loyal to your family. They are commoners who perform mundane tasks: one might be a stablehand, another a scribe, a third a herald who announces your arrival. These retainers will not fight for you or take actions that risk their lives, but they loyally perform non-dangerous tasks and can be sent to deliver messages, gather information, or handle logistical matters on your behalf.","description":"[PHB 2014 — Noble variant] You were raised in a household with a knightly tradition, trained in the arts of war and the expectations of courtly life. You bear the title of Knight by virtue of your birth, a deed of valor, or formal appointment by a lord. You are expected to uphold the chivalric ideals of your order or family — courage, honor, loyalty — even when it is inconvenient. Your family's honor and reputation are matters of great personal pride.","abv":""},
{"name":"Pirate","src":0,"skills":["Athletics","Perception"],"tools":["Navigator's tools","Vehicles (water)"],"languages":"—","equipment":"Belaying pin (club), 50 feet of silk rope, lucky charm (rabbit foot, small stone with a hole, or similar), common clothes, 10 gp","feature":"Bad Reputation","featureDesc":"[PHB 2014 — Sailor variant] If you spend at least 24 hours in a settlement, you can identify which people there are on the wrong side of the law. You can make contact with criminals and, as long as you don't undermine their trust, they will provide assistance that is not too dangerous or costly to them. Commoners and merchants are often too frightened of you to report your activities to authorities.","description":"[PHB 2014 — Sailor variant] You spent your years raiding ports, plundering ships, and living outside the law on the high seas. Violence and theft were your tools of the trade, and your ship was both home and fortress. You didn't serve a nation or obey its laws; you flew your own colors and answered to no one but your captain and your crew. The sea still calls to you, and old habits — including old enemies — are hard to shake.","abv":""},
{"name":"Archaeologist","src":4,"skills":["History","Survival"],"tools":["Cartographer's tools or Navigator's tools"],"languages":"One of your choice","equipment":"Cartographer's tools or navigator's tools, shovel, two-person tent, traveler's clothes, 25 gp","feature":"Historical Knowledge","featureDesc":"When you enter a ruin or dungeon, you can correctly ascertain its original purpose and builders — whether it was a dungeon, ruined city, tomb, temple, or palace — and roughly when it was constructed. In addition, you can determine the approximate monetary value of art objects more than a century old, and identify the culture or civilization that produced them.","description":"[ERLW — also in Tomb of Annihilation] You study the remnants of past civilizations — their monuments, artifacts, and buried cities. In Eberron, this means delving into pre-Galifar ruins, warforged scrap heaps from the Last War, and the ancient sites of the giants of Xen'drik. Part scientist, part adventurer, you crawl through collapsed towers and excavate buried chambers, piecing together history that others have forgotten or deliberately buried.","abv":""},
{"name":"Feylost","src":6,"skills":["Deception","Survival"],"tools":["One musical instrument of your choice"],"languages":"One of the following: Elvish, Gnomish, Goblin, or Sylvan","equipment":"Musical instrument (one of your choice), traveler's clothes, three trinkets (determined by the Feywild Trinkets table), 8 gp","feature":"Feywild Connection","featureDesc":"Your prolonged stay in the Feywild left an indelible mark on your psyche. You have a invisible Fey spirit guide — a pixie, sprite, or similar being — that only you can perceive. It occasionally delivers cryptic information or aid, but does so on its own schedule. Additionally, you have advantage on Charisma (Persuasion) checks when interacting with Fey creatures, and you can communicate simple ideas to them even without a shared language.","description":"[Wild Beyond the Witchlight / Spelljammer] You grew up in the Feywild after being spirited away from the mortal world as a child — perhaps taken by a hag, lured through a fairy ring, or simply lost and unable to find your way back. You spent years there, changed by its wild magic and capricious logic, before eventually returning to the Material Plane or finding your way to Wildspace. The Feywild's strange rules — emotion over reason, beauty over practicality, bargains over laws — still shape how you see the world.","abv":""},
{"name":"Pirate (Spelljammer)","src":6,"skills":["Athletics","Perception"],"tools":["Navigator's tools","Vehicles (space)"],"languages":"One of your choice","equipment":"Navigator's tools, silk rope (50 ft), common clothes with a distinctive captain's hat or headscarf, 10 gp","feature":"Bad Reputation (Space)","featureDesc":"Your reputation as a spacefaring pirate precedes you in Wildspace ports and on the Rock of Bral. You can find black market contacts, fences for stolen spelljammer components, and safe harbor in pirate-friendly asteroid settlements. Those who know your name give you a wide berth, and criminal elements in any Wildspace port are willing to deal with you — for a price.","description":"[Spelljammer: Adventures in Space] You sailed the void of Wildspace not as a merchant or explorer, but as a plunderer. Whether preying on trade routes between worlds, raiding remote space stations, or hunting specific quarry across the phlogiston, you lived by the code of the void: take what you can, trust nobody, and always have an escape route. The stars themselves are your hunting ground.","abv":""},
{"name":"Strixhaven — Lorehold Student","src":9,"skills":["History","Religion"],"tools":["Calligrapher's supplies"],"languages":"One of your choice","equipment":"Calligrapher's supplies, hammer and chisel, book of Lorehold lore, student's uniform, 15 gp","feature":"Lorehold's Answers","featureDesc":"You have access to Lorehold College's extensive library of historical records and can commune with the animated spirit manifestations of historical figures that Lorehold mages conjure. Once per day, you can ask such a spirit a brief historical question; the DM provides a truthful but possibly cryptic answer drawn from that figure's knowledge and perspective.","description":"[Strixhaven: A Curriculum of Chaos — TCE] You studied at Lorehold College, the college of archaeomancy at the renowned Strixhaven University. Lorehold mages blend history with magic, animating the spirits of ancient warriors, scholars, and rulers to learn directly from the dead. Your studies shaped your understanding of time, civilization, cause and effect, and the magic that binds past to present. You believe that understanding history is the key to shaping the future.","abv":""},
{"name":"Strixhaven — Prismari Student","src":9,"skills":["Acrobatics","Performance"],"tools":["One musical instrument of your choice"],"languages":"One of your choice","equipment":"Musical instrument (one of your choice), sketchbook of elemental art studies, student's uniform, 15 gp","feature":"Elemental Artistry","featureDesc":"Your training at Prismari has given you the ability to use elemental magic in small, performative ways. Once per long rest, you can create a harmless elemental spectacle — a burst of flame, spray of water, gust of wind, or shower of sparks — as part of an artistic performance. This display can captivate an audience for up to 1 minute and leaves onlookers with a strong impression of you.","description":"[Strixhaven: A Curriculum of Chaos — TCE] You studied at Prismari College, the college of elemental arts. Prismari students combine elemental magic with creative expression — wielding fire, water, and lightning as paint and brushstrokes. Every performance is both art and spellwork. Your performances are breathtaking, occasionally dangerous, and always memorable. You believe that the greatest magic is magic that moves the soul.","abv":""},
{"name":"Strixhaven — Quandrix Student","src":9,"skills":["Arcana","Nature"],"tools":["Navigator's tools"],"languages":"One of your choice","equipment":"Navigator's tools, abacus, notebook filled with mathematical theorems and diagrams, student's uniform, 15 gp","feature":"Numerical Insight","featureDesc":"Your mathematical training at Quandrix gives you insight into patterns and probabilities. Once per long rest, you can make an Intelligence (Arcana) or Intelligence (Nature) check (DC 15) to determine the statistical likelihood of a future event, predict the behavior of a natural system (weather patterns, wildlife migration, structural stability), or identify a hidden mathematical pattern in a magical or natural phenomenon.","description":"[Strixhaven: A Curriculum of Chaos — TCE] You studied at Quandrix College, where mages use advanced mathematics to manipulate the fundamental structure of reality. Quandrix students study the fractal patterns that underlie both nature and magic, using theorems and proofs as spells. You believe that the universe is built on numbers, and if you can understand the equation, you can change the result.","abv":""},
{"name":"Strixhaven — Silverquill Student","src":9,"skills":["Intimidation","Persuasion"],"tools":["Calligrapher's supplies"],"languages":"One of your choice","equipment":"Calligrapher's supplies, journal of speeches and essays, ink pen with silver nib, student's uniform, 15 gp","feature":"Words Have Power","featureDesc":"Your training in the magic of words gives you a decisive edge in social situations. Once per short rest, when you succeed on a Charisma (Persuasion) or Charisma (Intimidation) check, you can choose to have your words linger with particular potency — the target remains positively or fearfully inclined toward you for 1 hour, even if you part ways, unless you or your companions do something to actively undermine that impression.","description":"[Strixhaven: A Curriculum of Chaos — TCE] You studied at Silverquill College, the college of eloquence and shadow. Silverquill mages wield the power of words as weapons and shields — inspiring allies with radiant speeches or cutting enemies down with shadow-laced insults laced with genuine magical force. Sharp of mind and sharper of tongue, you believe that the right words at the right moment can accomplish what swords cannot.","abv":""},
{"name":"Strixhaven — Witherbloom Student","src":9,"skills":["Medicine","Nature"],"tools":["Herbalism kit"],"languages":"One of your choice","equipment":"Herbalism kit, distinctive black coat, collection of preserved plant and animal specimens in glass vials, student's uniform, 15 gp","feature":"Life's Balance","featureDesc":"Your training in the magic of life and death gives you insight into biological processes. Once per short rest, you can spend 1 minute carefully examining a creature to determine its general state of health, identify any diseases or poisons currently affecting it, sense approximately how close to death it is, and identify whether it has been recently subjected to necromantic or healing magic.","description":"[Strixhaven: A Curriculum of Chaos — TCE] You studied at Witherbloom College, where mages draw on the raw essence of life and death from swamps, bogs, and decaying places. Witherbloom mages are utterly pragmatic about mortality — life feeds on death, and they have learned to use both sides of that equation. Equal parts healer and necrotic threat, you don't flinch at the grim realities of existence, and you understand that decay is simply transformation by another name.","abv":""},
{"name":"Fisher","src":9,"skills":["History","Survival"],"tools":["Vehicles (water)"],"languages":"One of your choice","equipment":"Fishing tackle, a net, a favorite fishing lure or hand-carved hook, a set of traveler's clothes, 10 gp","feature":"Harvest the Water","featureDesc":"You can always find sufficient food and fresh water for yourself and up to five other people each day, provided you have access to a body of water that contains fish. You know how to read weather signs and tidal patterns, and you can navigate reliably by stars over open water. Other fisherfolk and sailors treat you as one of their own, sharing gossip and local knowledge freely.","description":"[Icewind Dale: Rime of the Frostmaiden] You have spent much of your life working a net, rod, or fishing line — on sea, lake, or river. You've seen the water in all its moods: glassy calm at dawn, whipped to fury by winter storms, frozen solid under feet of ice. You have a patient, methodical nature that others sometimes mistake for slowness, and a deep knowledge of tides, currents, seasons, and the creatures that live beneath the surface.","abv":""}
];
